<!-- ============= Introduction ============================== -->
<!-- Use the Introduction section to give a brief overview of what
     the applet is and what it does. -->
    <sect1 id="gcdemu-introduction">
        <title>Introduction</title> 
	 <!-- You should start the Introduction with a screenshot of the applet in a panel -->
<!-- ==== Figure ============================================= -->
        <figure id="gcdemu-fig">
            <title>&applet; Applet</title>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-applet.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <textobject>
                        <phrase>
                            Shows &applet; applet.
                        </phrase>
                    </textobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
        </figure> 
<!-- ==== End of Figure ======================================= -->
        <para>
            The <application>&applet;</application> applet is a GNOME applet for
            controlling CDEmu daemon. It is part of the userspace-cdemu suite, a 
            free, GPL CD/DVD-ROM device emulator for linux.
        </para>
        <para>  
            It provides a graphic interface that allows performing the key tasks 
            related to controlling the CDEmu daemon, such as loading and unloading 
            devices, displaying devices' status and retrieving/setting devices' 
            debug masks. It supports connection on both system and session bus.
        </para>
        <para>
            In addition, applet listens to the signals emitted by CDEmu daemon 
            and provides the notification via libnotify's notifications (provided 
            that python bindings are installed).
        </para>
        <sect2 id="gcdemu-introduction-add">
            <title>To Add &applet; to a Panel</title>
            <para>Perform the following steps:</para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        Right-click on the panel.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        Choose <guimenuitem>Add to Panel</guimenuitem>.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                <para>
                    Scroll down the list of items in the <guilabel>Add to Panel</guilabel> dialog, then select <guilabel>gCDEmu Applet</guilabel>.
                </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        Click <guibutton>Add</guibutton>.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </sect2>
    </sect1>
<!-- ================ Usage ================================ -->
<!-- Use this section to describe how to use the applet to perform the tasks for 
     which the applet is designed. -->
    <sect1 id="gcdemu-usage">
        <title>Usage</title>
        <para>
            When you add <application>&applet;</application> to a panel, its icon
            might be either a color or a greyed-out one. This indicates the state of
            the applet; when applet is successfully connected to the daemon, it is
            active and its icon is colored. When connection has failed for some reason
            or the daemon is shut down, the applet is inactive and its icon is greyed-out.
        </para>
        <para>
            <figure id="gcdemu-fig1">
                <title>Active applet</title> 
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig1" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <textobject>
                            <phrase>Screen shot of an active applet</phrase>
                        </textobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </figure>
            <figure id="gcdemu-fig2">
                <title>Inactive applet</title> 
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig2" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <textobject>
                            <phrase>Screen shot of an inactive applet</phrase>
                        </textobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </figure>
        </para>
        <para>
            The state of applet changes when daemon emits appropriate signal (i.e.
            when it is started or when it is properly stopped). Alternatively, the
            state can also change after a command has been sent to daemon fails. In
            this case, applet attempts to verify the connection, and upon failure 
            enters inactive state. This might happen if daemon crashes.
        </para>
        <para>
            If you wish to change the applet's icon, you can do so by manually editing 
            applet's <guilabel>icon_name</guilabel> G-Conf key. Please note that icon 
            name is relative to gCDEmu's pixmap dir (i.e. /usr/share/pixmaps/gcdemu).
        </para>
<!-- ================ Usage Subsection ================================ -->
        <sect2 id="gcdemu-usage-menu">
            <title>Device menu</title>
            <para>
                When applet is in active state, a left click on its icon results
                in a device menu being displayed. It contains one entry per each
                virtual device, showing their current status.
            </para>
            <figure id="applet-fig3">
                <title>Device menu</title>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig3" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <textobject>
                            <phrase>
                                Screen shot of the device menu.
                            </phrase>
                        </textobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </figure>
        </sect2>
<!-- ================ Usage Subsection ================================ -->
        <sect2 id="gcdemu-usage-quick">
            <title>Quick loading and unloading</title>
            <para>
                Quick device loading/unloading can be done by left-clicking on 
                the device entry in device menu. 
            </para>
            <para>
                If clicked on empty device, a file selection dialog will appear,
                allowing you to select image file(s), which the applet will then 
                attempted to load.
            </para>
            <para>
                If clicked on a loaded device, the applet will attempt to unload
                the device.
            </para>
            <para>
                Note that both loading and unloading can fail, and corresponding
                error is displayed in error dialog.
            </para>
        </sect2>
<!-- ================ Usage Subsection ================================ -->
        <sect2 id="gcdemu-usage-devdiag">
            <title>Device properties dialog</title>
            <para>
                Device properties dialog can be obtained by right-clicking on 
                the device entry in device menu. It has multiple tabs which 
                allow you to load and unload device and change device's options,
                such as device's ID, debug masks or DPM and transfer rate 
                emulation flags.
            </para>
            
            <sect3 id="gcdemu-usage-devdiag-load">
                <title>Loading and unloading</title>
                <para>
                    The <guilabel>Status</guilabel> tab shows the current device
                    status and allows you to load or unload the device.
                </para>
                <para>
                    In addition, you can find information on device mapping in
                    <guilabel>Device mapping</guilabel> frame. It displays 
                    information on which SCSI CD-ROM device and which SCSI generic
                    device correspond to the given CDEmu device (if this information 
                    is provided by daemon). This can be useful for example if you 
                    need to pass the path of the CDEmu device to a command-line 
                    application, like mplayer.
                </para>
                <figure id="applet-fig4">
                    <title>Device tab of an empty device</title>
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig4" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <textobject>
                                <phrase>
                                    Screen shot of a <guilabel>Status</guilabel> tab of an empty device.
                                </phrase>
                            </textobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </figure>
                <para>
                    To load the device, click on the <guilabel>Load</guilabel> 
                    button and a file selection dialog will appear, allowing you to select
                    image file(s).
                </para>
                <para>
                    If loading succeeds, device's status is updated.
                </para>
                <figure id="applet-fig5">
                    <title>Device tab of a loaded device</title>
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig5" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <textobject>
                                <phrase>
                                    Screen shot of a <guilabel>Status</guilabel> tab of a loaded device.
                                </phrase>
                            </textobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </figure>
                <para>
                    To unload the device, click on the <guilabel>Unload</guilabel> 
                    button.
                </para>
                
                <sect4 id="gcdemu-usage-devdiag-load-password">
                    <title>Loading encrypted images</title>
                    <para>
                        If the image you are trying to load is encrypted (protected
                        by password), gCDEmu will prompt you to enter it.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="applet-fig11">
                    <title>Password prompt dialog</title>
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig11" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <textobject>
                                <phrase>
                                    Screen shot of a <guilabel>Status</guilabel> tab of a loaded device.
                                </phrase>
                            </textobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                    </figure>
                    <para>
                        Entered password is then sent to the daemon.
                    </para>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Note, however, that the password is sent over D-BUS in 
                        a plain string form, without any protection. Depending 
                        on your privacy concerns you might wish to avoid loading 
                        such images.</para>
                    </warning>
                </sect4>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="gcdemu-usage-devdiag-options">
                <title>Device options</title>
                <para>
                    The <guilabel>Options</guilabel> tab allows you to control
                    device's options. Currently, these are:
                    <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem><para>Device ID</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>DPM emulation flag</para></listitem>
                        <listitem><para>Transfer rate emulation flag</para></listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </para>
                <figure id="applet-fig10">
                    <title>Options tab</title>
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig10" format="PNG"/>
                            </imageobject>
                            <textobject>
                                <phrase>
                                    Screen shot of <guilabel>Options</guilabel> tab.
                                </phrase>
                            </textobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </figure>
                <para>
                    Currently set device ID values are displayed in text entries
                    within <guilabel>Device ID</guilabel> frame. To change device
                    ID, change the values and click on the <guilabel>Set device 
                    ID</guilabel> button.
                </para>
                <para>
                    To change the value of DPM emulation flag, simply check/uncheck
                    <guilabel>DPM emulation</guilabel> checkbox.
                </para>
                <para>
                    To change the value of transfer rate emulation flag, simply 
                    check/uncheck <guilabel>Transfer rate emulation</guilabel> 
                    checkbox.
                </para>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="gcdemu-usage-devdiag-debug">
                <title>Debug masks manipulation</title>
                <para>
                    <application>&applet;</application> applet has a simple and
                    efficient way of manipulating device's debug masks.
                </para>
                <para>
                    To manipulate the verbosity of the daemon part, select the
                    <guilabel>Daemon</guilabel> tab.
                    
                    <figure id="applet-fig6">
                        <title>Daemon debug mask tab</title>
                        <screenshot>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig6" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                                <textobject>
                                    <phrase>
                                        Screen shot of a <guilabel>Daemon</guilabel> debug mask tab.
                                    </phrase>
                                </textobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </screenshot>
                    </figure>
                </para>
                <para>
                    To manipulate the verbosity of libMirage library, select the
                    <guilabel>Library</guilabel> tab.
                    
                    <figure id="applet-fig7">
                        <title>Library debug mask tab</title>
                        <screenshot>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig7" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                                <textobject>
                                    <phrase>
                                        Screen shot of a <guilabel>Library</guilabel> debug mask tab.
                                    </phrase>
                                </textobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </screenshot>
                    </figure>
                </para>
                <para>
                    Currently set debug mask is displayed in form of appropriately
                    checked and unchecked check boxes. If you wish to change the
                    mask, simply check/uncheck appropriate check boxes and click
                    on the <guilabel>Set debug mask</guilabel> button.
                </para>
                <para>
                    Note that all appropriate device properties are updated and
                    displayed when the applet receives notification from the daemon.
                    This means that they get updated even if the change is faciliated
                    from another client.
                </para>
            </sect3>
        </sect2>
    </sect1>
<!-- ============= Customization ============================= -->
<!-- Use this section to describe how to customize the applet. -->
    <sect1 id="gcdemu-prefs">
        <title>Settings</title>
        <para>
            For the time being, there are two settings to be set in 
            <application>&applet;</application>. 
        </para>
        <para>
            The first one is whether the applet should display notifications 
            from daemon or not; it is available only if pynotify module is available.
        </para>
        <para>
            The second setting is whether the applet should use system bus to
            connect to daemon; if it is not set, the applet uses session bus.
        </para>
<!-- =============== Customization Subsection ================ -->
<!-- Use a new section to describe different tabbed sections on the Settings or Preferences
     dialog. -->
     <sect2 id="gcdemu-prefs-system-bus">
            <title>System/session bus</title> 
            <para>
                You can set the applet to use system/session bus to connect to daemon
                by right clicking on the applet icon and selecting <guilabel>Use system 
                bus</guilabel> menu item. If the item is checked, system 
                bus is used, otherwise session bus is used.
            </para>
            <figure id="applet-fig8">
                <title>Applet menu with highligthed <guilabel>Use system bus</guilabel> menu item</title>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig8" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <textobject>
                            <phrase>
                                Screen shot of the applet menu, showing the highligthed
                                <guilabel>Use system bus</guilabel> menu item.
                            </phrase>
                        </textobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </figure>
        </sect2>
        
        <sect2 id="gcdemu-prefs-notifications">
            <title>Enabling/Disabling notifications</title> 
            <para>
                You can enable/disable notifications by right clicking on the applet
                icon and selecting <guilabel>Show Notifications</guilabel> menu item. 
                If checked, notifications are enabled, otherwise they are disabled.
            </para>
            <figure id="applet-fig9">
                <title>Applet menu with highligthed <guilabel>Show Notifications</guilabel> menu item</title>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/gcdemu-fig9" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <textobject>
                            <phrase>
                                Screen shot of the applet menu, showing the highligthed
                                <guilabel>Show Notifications</guilabel> menu item.
                            </phrase>
                        </textobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </figure>
        </sect2>
    </sect1>
